<br>
everwhere you look people try to bash the xbox for lack of games.  in its first year there have been more good games for the xbox than for the ps2 in its first year.  i bought 2 games at ps2 launch, didnt by another one for nearly 8 months.  xbox, one year later, i already have over 12.  gamecube comes in last with 3.  besides, splinter cell and fables alone should trump most any other game on the other systems.  and like was stated before, any cross-platform game will look better on the xbox, and will often have extra levels and goodies.<br>
<br>
for me, the xbox wins every category of comparability, save maybe portability.  graphics, multi/online play, value (id rather pay the extra $50 and get the xbox specs over the gamecube any day), storage, etc.  <br>
<br>
and to the pc gamer crowd, try to remember that not everyone can buy a descent computer with hardware that meets min req and continually upgrade and patch.  some people just want to buy a system that plays games and sit on their couch and never do anything until the next system comes along.  i could buy a xbox, ps2, and gamecube for the price of a low end computer that probably couldnt even handle unreal 2003.  sidenote, the person that said halo on consoles is horrid, most of my friends that are sans computers would disagree.  console gamers playing fps on computers are actually more pathetic than pc gamers playing them on consoles.  <br>
<br>
i enjoy ALL my systems, even the gamecube and the three games worth buying to me (for now).  all three have great games coming out in the next 2 or 3 months, and any console gamer would, or at least should, be happy with any of them.<br>
<br>
end console bigotry! buy them all!  <br>
<br>
